I love, love love Yoga with Adriene‚Ä¶been following her 30 day classes for over a year.
I wondered if anyone has any inner pelvic floor burn when doing yoga sessions? I will be 54 in a couple of weeks and mid menopause. I suffer from IBS and Intersistial cystitis so use yoga as a way to switch my body off from these ongoing pains. The only worry I have is I‚Äôve noticed my flare ups tend to be worse after a yoga session. :(

I had to stop yoga for the last two day. As we are in the throes of a huge transition on this planet and being flooded with divine feminine energy, my whole right side has been stiff and sore and a bit stuck. I think I may have just a few things that need letting go of and healing. Even though I am feeling the 'stuck' energy I engaged in everything. When Adriene said towards the end about how we are told what to look at, where to be, what to eat, it made me cry. The Truth of that rang through me. I so look forward to this great awakening we are all going through at this time and to experience our new earth and our freedom! Thank you Adriene.

I'm a musician and I used to do yoga three times a day, even teach yoga, but a long period of time I lost track of both music and yoga two core important things for me. Lately I'd do yoga for 5 minutes or 30 now and then, but never allowing myself to _really_ connect. Today I wanted to be true to myself and I decided to put on some music to this class and somehow it felt almost like a mindful dance with and for myself. The vinyasas felt smooth and honest and I could go deeper into poses like I haven't in years. I was angry and sad before I started and I forgot all about it. I was just here. I felt so true to myself and open to something bigger. 

This one was important. So very important. It also reminds me of the things we might see if we decide to stick with it. ‚ù§Ô∏è Can't wait for day 10.

For anyone wondering "Are there really people practicing all around the world with me?", think about this.
When I watched this video, it had been out for 18 hours, with 82, 914 views.
There are 64800 seconds in 18 hours.
That means if you watched it, someone else was definitely watching with you (it might have been me).
Chances aren't bad that they started watching it the very second you did.
And that's not counting all the people doing yoga who aren't watching this video.
And that's not counting all the people who have chosen to be mindful of their breath, of the present moment.
And that's not counting all the people simply breathing at the same time as you, whether they're aware of it or not.

Now that's community.

"This too shall pass" is something that keeps popping into my head during this journey.

On the 1st, a glass pot lid exploded on me and filleted a hunk off my finger. I was in a car accident a few days ago. An unexpected bill popped up which puts me way under budget. What feels like a lot of unexpected and unavoidable bad news has appeared for me in just this last week.

The way I have begun to see it, it already has passed. The finger is healed, it just hasn't (fully) happened yet. The car is already fixed. I just haven't experienced that moment yet. Even these 30 days of yoga are already complete, it just hasn't come to pass yet. I'm still living in this moment because it's worth experiencing.

On the flip side, I have received a sudden flood of good news. I landed a part-time job at a dog daycare place. Chill with dogs for work? Yes please. I'm a freelance animator as well. I received word that I have about 4 great gigs coming my way very soon. I met with a drummer and another guitarist. I'm finally getting a band together!

This too shall pass.

How will I handle that? When the good news also comes to pass, will I move through it with grace?

I haven't in the past. I think this is my time. This is what I'm dedicating myself to understanding; all things good, bad, or mild will move on, and I can choose to handle it with grace and ease or I can let it dismantle me.

That's my long comment for the 30 days!ü§ò

Today, I kept noticing the sky as it changed from night blue to a flashy marine blue; almost surreal, to a light purple, and now a nice clear morning blue. I smiled as I thought to myself "I'm connecting to the skies, to the highest colours I can perceive". I choose to let this blue light lift me up today. 
I love Thursdays. Thursday is the day I get to do my relaxation activity on the lunch break with the kids at school. I have a group of 15 children, from 6 to 11  years old, who spend an hour with me in an introductory session to meditation, conscious breathing, yoga, and then we end with massages and a discussion (of which they choose the theme). I love spending that time with them. They are so... real. They don't censure themselves, they try anything and everything, and they are curious and fast-learners at these ages. 
Anyway, focusing back on this practice, I noticed how my toes now automatically do the opposite of griping on the mat, by lifting. I remember one of the first video I watched (Yoga for Back Pain), when Adriene said "Notice your sensations and thoughts, you will want to remember where you started this journey". I'm amazed at the increased mindfulness I have, noticing parts of my body I used to ignore where even there ! I am sooo full of love and happiness today ! I send it in thoughts to you, people. Know that waves of positive energy are coming you way ! Pass it on, if you may, or cherish the thought, cherish you own smile <3 
Love (from France).
